@startuml Node_State_Diagram
!theme plain
title Node State Transitions and Lifecycle

state "WAKE" as wake {
    state "Active" : Clock, Tranceiver\nand Protocol ticking
}

state "SLEEP" as sleep {
    state "Idle" : Only Clock ticking\nLow power mode
}

state "DEAD" as dead {
    state "Inactive" : Battery depleted\nNo operations
}

[*] --> wake : Node initialized

wake --> sleep : Transition to\nsleep mode
sleep --> wake : Transition to\nwake mode

wake --> dead : Battery depleted\n(is_dead() = True)
sleep --> dead : Battery depleted\n(is_dead() = True)

dead --> wake : Battery\nrecharged\n(is_dead() = False)

note right of wake
  Power consumption from:
  - Clock
  - Transceiver
  - Protocol
end note

note right of sleep
  Reduced power consumption:
  - Only Clock
  - Tranceiver and Protocol\n  in standby
end note

note right of dead
  Zero power consumption:
  - All modules reset
  - Await recharge
end note

@enduml
